description:
After C2 lands, drop the tellerLib + inlined tellerRegistry block from turnkey's own 'turnkey.toolchains = { ... }' configuration in flake.nix. The block becomes:

  turnkey.toolchains = {
    enable = true;
    declarationFiles = {
      default = ./toolchain.toml;
      docs = ./docs/toolchain.toml;
    };
    registryExtensions = ...; # keep — turnkey-specific tools
    buck2 = ...;              # keep
  };

Also check whether the packages.turnkey-prelude block at flake.nix:103 can reuse self.lib.defaultTellerRegistry (it currently inlines the same overlaidPkgs construction). Probably yes — and would close another duplication.

Verify: 'nix develop' still produces the same dev shell; tk build //src/python/... still works.
